---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LifeCard from '../components/LifeCard.astro';
import { BookOpen, Hammer, Moon, Mail, Link } from '@lucide/astro';
---

<Layout>
  <header
    class="hero min-vh-100 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center text-center px-3 position-relative"
    data-parallax
    style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(15, 27, 46, 0.75), rgba(15, 27, 46, 0.85)), url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1602376531381-e2bc41a27f74?fm=jpg&q=80&w=1600&auto=format&fit=crop');"
  >
    <div class="container position-relative">
      <h1 class="mb-3" data-reveal>Kirikla Monastery</h1>
      <h2 class="h4 mb-4 fw-medium" data-reveal>The only Orthodox men's monastery in Estonia</h2>
      <p class="lead max-w-prose mx-auto mb-5" data-reveal>
        A living place of prayer, work, and monastic community — rooted in the tradition of Mount Athos.
      </p>
      <div class="d-flex flex-column flex-sm-row justify-content-center gap-3" data-reveal>
        <a href="#donate" class="btn btn-primary px-4 py-2">Support the Monastery</a>
        <a href="#visiting" class="btn btn-outline-light px-4 py-2">Visit the Monastery</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container max-w-content py-5 my-5">
    <section id="intro" class="text-center mb-5 pb-5" data-reveal>
      <p class="fs-5">
        Kirikla Monastery was founded in 2025 under the guidance of Bishop Damaskinos of Haapsalu, a member of the
        brotherhood of Xenophontos Monastery on Mount Athos. The monastery is home to a small brotherhood of monks
        who have dedicated their lives to prayer and service to God.
      </p>
      <p class="fs-5 mb-0">Visitors, pilgrims, and friends of the monastery are always welcome.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider mb-5"></div>

    <section id="history" class="py-5 my-4" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="text-center mb-5">Our History</h2>
      <p>
        For centuries, the Petseri (Pskov-Pechory) Monastery served as the spiritual center of Estonia's Orthodox
        Christians. After independence, the monastery remained on the Russian side of the border, and monastic life
        within the Estonian Orthodox Church came to an end.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2024, Hieromonk Damaskinos — a member of the brotherhood of Xenophontos Monastery on Mount Athos — was
        elected Bishop of Haapsalu, bringing with him a deep wish to establish a men's monastery and carry the
        spiritual tradition of Mount Athos to Estonia.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2026, entrepreneur Urmas Sõõrumaa's generosity gave the brotherhood a home: a property in Kirikla, Harju
        County, 40 kilometres from Tallinn. Until construction is complete, the brotherhood lives temporarily at the
        nearby Üiso Farm, which now houses the monastery chapel and living quarters.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2025, the first monk of the brotherhood, Father Paisios, was tonsured — ordained to the diaconate in 2026.
        A second brother has since joined as a novice.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 fst-italic text-center text-secondary-emphasis">
        We pray that God will bless the growth of this young brotherhood and bring the monastery to completion.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider mb-5"></div>

    <section id="life" class="py-5 my-4" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="text-center mb-5">Life at the Monastery</h2>
      <p class="text-center mb-5">In a monastery, the day is divided into three parts: prayer, work, and rest.</p>

      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1627573897879-1eff66f2c228?fm=jpg&q=80&w=1600&auto=format&fit=crop"
        alt="Cathedral interior with gilded icons"
        class="img-fluid rounded w-100 object-fit-cover mb-5"
        style="max-height: 400px;"
      />

      <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Prayer">
            <BookOpen slot="icon" size={20} />
            Both communal and private — practiced in one's own cell and in the earliest hours of morning, when night
            is considered the best time to seek God.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Work">
            <Hammer slot="icon" size={20} />
            Sustains the monastery and teaches the meaning of effort — from cleaning, kitchen, and garden work to
            icon painting and construction.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <LifeCard title="Rest">
            <Moon slot="icon" size={20} />
            Deliberately scarce. Monks rise at dawn, choosing prayer over comfort.
          </LifeCard>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="px-lg-5 text-center">
        Kirikla Monastery is coenobitic — a communal life where no one holds private property, and the monastery
        provides for all. The brotherhood is like a family: bound by mutual love, obedience, and a shared calling
        that traces its roots to Mount Athos.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="divider mb-5"></div>

    <section id="visiting" class="py-5 my-4 text-center" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="mb-4">Visiting</h2>
      <p class="max-w-prose mx-auto mb-4">
        Monasteries are places of spiritual retreat. You are welcome to come and see the chapel, enjoy the
        surroundings, or simply rest for a while. The monastery does not yet have regular opening hours, but we are
        always glad to welcome visitors by prior arrangement.
      </p>
      <a
        href="mailto:kirikla.klooster@gmail.com"
        class="text-decoration-none d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2 fw-semibold"
      >
        <Mail size={18} /> kirikla.klooster@gmail.com
      </a>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section id="donate" class="bg-secondary py-5" data-reveal>
    <div class="container max-w-content py-5">
      <div class="row align-items-center g-5">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4">Support the Brotherhood</h2>
          <p class="mb-4">
            Since the monks give up their possessions and dedicate their entire lives to serving God, donations are
            essential to covering the daily needs of the monastery. Kirikla Monastery also has major construction
            projects ahead that will require significant funds. We are grateful for every donation, whether large or
            small.
          </p>

          <div class="mb-4 p-3 border border-dark-subtle rounded">
            <h3 class="h6 text-primary mb-2">Estonian Bank Details</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled m-0 small">
              <li><strong>Beneficiary:</strong> Eesti Apostlik-Õigeusu Kiriku Püha Mäe Isade Püha Klooster Kiriklas</li>
              <li><strong>Bank:</strong> Swedbank</li>
              <li><strong>IBAN:</strong> EE402200221094185846</li>
              <li><strong>SWIFT/BIC:</strong> HABAEE2X</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-4 p-3 border border-dark-subtle rounded">
            <h3 class="h6 text-primary mb-2">For Donors in the United States</h3>
            <p class="m-0 small">
              Donate through "Friends of Lintuvuori Co." (tax-exempt in the USA), supporting monastic life and
              Athonite spirituality in Finland and Estonia.
            </p>
            <p class="m-0 small mt-2">
              <strong>Pay to the Order of:</strong> Friends of Lintuvuori Co.<br />
              <strong>Memo:</strong> donation<br />
              <strong>Mail to:</strong> Attorney Tim Barkley, One Park Ave., Suite 2A, P.O. Box 1136, Mount Airy, MD
              21771
            </p>
          </div>

          <a href="mailto:kirikla.klooster@gmail.com" class="btn btn-primary px-5 py-2 w-100 w-sm-auto">Donate Now</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <img
            src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601231656153-73aa7f115365?fm=jpg&q=80&w=1600&auto=format&fit=crop"
            alt="Lit candles before an icon"
            class="img-fluid rounded w-100 object-fit-cover shadow-lg"
            style="min-height: 400px;"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="bg-dark py-5 border-top border-dark-subtle">
    <div class="container max-w-content py-4">
      <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <h2 class="h4 mb-3">Kirikla Monastery</h2>
          <address class="small fst-normal opacity-75 mb-3">
            Eesti Apostlik-Õigeusu Kiriku Püha Mäe Isade Püha Klooster Kiriklas<br />
            Üiso, Pihali küla, Kohila vald<br />
            79703 Rapla maakond, Estonia
          </address>
          <a href="mailto:kirikla.klooster@gmail.com" class="text-decoration-none small d-block mb-2">
            kirikla.klooster@gmail.com
          </a>
          <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none small d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2">
            <Link size={16} /> Follow Kirikla Monastery on Facebook
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 text-md-end">
          <p class="small opacity-75 mb-2">
            <strong>Abbot:</strong> His Grace, Bishop Damaskinos of Haapsalu —
            <a href="mailto:damaskinos@eoc.ee" class="text-decoration-none">damaskinos@eoc.ee</a>
          </p>
          <p class="small opacity-75 mb-0">
            <strong>Languages spoken:</strong><br />
            Estonian, Finnish, Swedish, Greek, English, German, French
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
    import '../lib/reveal.js';
  </script>
</Layout>
